        "content": "<p>FYI, <code>{i}ᶜ</code> is preferable to <code>Finset.univ \\ {i}</code>.</p>",
        "id": 567246285,
        "sender_full_name": "Miyahara Kō",
        "timestamp": 1767986124
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><del>When it is used as <code>simp</code> or <code>grind</code> lemmas.</del> (even if it isn't used as <code>simp</code> or <code>grind</code> lemma)</p>",
        "id": 567246405,
        "sender_full_name": "Miyahara Kō",
        "timestamp": 1767986158
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"569722\">Miyahara Kō</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Lemma.20about.20Finite.20Linear.20Ordered.20type/near/567246285\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>FYI, <code>{i}ᶜ</code> is preferable to <code>Finset.univ \\ {i}</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What are the benefits of using compl?</p>",
        "id": 567288684,
        "sender_full_name": "Edison Xie",
        "timestamp": 1768014154
    },
    {
        "content": "<ol>\n<li>There are far more <a href=\"https://loogle.lean-lang.org/?q=%28_%E1%B6%9C+%3A+Finset+_%29\"><code>Finset</code> lemmas for <code>sᶜ</code></a> than <a href=\"https://loogle.lean-lang.org/?q=Finset.univ+%5C+_\">ones for <code>Finset.univ \\ s</code></a>.</li>\n<li>Rewriting <code>x ∈ sᶜ</code> to <code>x ∉ s</code> requires only one lemma(<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.mem_compl#doc\">docs#Finset.mem_compl</a>), rewriting <code>x ∈ Finset.univ \\ s</code> to <code>x ∉ s</code> requires three lemmas(<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.mem_sdiff#doc\">docs#Finset.mem_sdiff</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.mem_univ#doc\">docs#Finset.mem_univ</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=true_and#doc\">docs#true_and</a>).</li>\n<li>It is consistent with the <code>Set</code> lemma (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Set.Iio_union_Ioi#doc\">docs#Set.Iio_union_Ioi</a>).</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 567300275,
        "sender_full_name": "Miyahara Kō",
        "timestamp": 1768029716
    }
